    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <head>42. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d42fn1">Source:
                        Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79–01025A, Box 76, Folder 2. Secret.
                        Prepared on August 20.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-19"
                        >August 19, 1953</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_PBFORTUNE1">PBFORTUNE</gloss>—Meeting with <gloss
                            target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss> at 1300 on 19 August</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Tom Mann</persName> called <gloss
                            target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss> subsequent to meeting in my apartment on
                        17 August to say he had seen <persName corresp="#p_SGWBS1">General
                            Smith</persName> and informed him of our meeting. <persName
                            corresp="#p_SGWBS1">General Smith</persName> was favorably inclined to
                        positive and constructive suggestions made for softening up. Since <persName
                            corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName> is leaving for Greece today, he
                        recommended a substitute to <persName corresp="#p_SGWBS1">General
                            Smith</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_LRG1">Ray Leddy</persName>, in
                        charge of Central American Republics. <persName corresp="#p_LRG1"
                            >Leddy</persName> was approved by <persName corresp="#p_SGWBS1">General
                            Smith</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName> said he
                        had briefed <persName corresp="#p_LRG1">Leddy</persName> with the General’s
                            <pb facs="0120" n="90" xml:id="pg_90"/> approval, including the fact
                        that only <persName corresp="#p_SGWBS1">General Smith</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_LRG1">Leddy</persName> will be cut in. No other
                        echelons or personalities of ARA will be informed.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss> said the Acting Director wanted a quick
                        check with <persName corresp="#p_ECS1">Col. Edwards</persName> on <persName
                            corresp="#p_LRG1">Leddy</persName>. I called <persName corresp="#p_ECS1"
                            >Colonel Edwards</persName>, who checked <persName corresp="#p_LRG1"
                            >Leddy</persName>’s file and at 1520 gave full and unqualified
                        clearance. He said that <persName corresp="#p_LRG1">Leddy</persName>’s
                        record was highly favorable, in fact, outstanding. I informed <gloss
                            target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss>’s secretary, who in turn called me at 1650
                        with the following message from <gloss target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss>—“Fine.
                        Go ahead.”</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KCJC1">
                            <hi rend="strong">J.C. King</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <gloss target="#t_CWH1">
                        <hi rend="italic">CWH</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
